DentAI Backend — Production Architecture Plan
Decision: Full breaking change (new response envelope). Frontend integration updated in same pass. Data: Pre-launch only — clean migrations permitted, column renames/drops safe.

Context
The backend is a functional MVP that handles real dental clinic workflows but was built for speed, not production. The audit identified 5 critical security vulnerabilities (IDOR on visits/appointments), no role-based access control, dentist_id used as the authorization boundary (wrong — clinic_id must be), GET endpoints that mutate state, no input validation, readFileSync on 25 MB files, N+1 queries, and an AI layer that silently returns fake data on failure.

This plan transforms it incrementally into a production-grade backend: secure, consistently authorized at the clinic level, validated, paginated, with a clean repository layer separating DB concerns from controllers, and a standard response envelope across all endpoints.

Guiding principle: Every write touches exactly what it needs to — no speculative abstractions, no features beyond the audit's identified gaps.

Authorization Model (The Core Architectural Rule)
Old:  WHERE dentist_id = req.dentistId   ← WRONG for multi-staff
New:  WHERE clinic_id  = req.clinicId    ← RIGHT

dentist_id  = audit trail only (who created it)
clinic_id   = authorization boundary (who can see it)
req.role    = operation permission (what they can do)
Request Flow (Layered Monolith)
HTTP Request
    ↓
Route (express router — path + method only)
    ↓
Middleware (requestId → auth → requireClinic → requireRole → validate)
    ↓
Controller (receive, call service, return response — NO DB calls)
    ↓
Transaction Service (orchestrate multi-step operations, enforce business rules)
    ↓
Repository (clinic-scoped DB access — NO business logic)
    ↓
Supabase (DB + Storage)
This is a Modular Monolith — one deployable, one process, clean internal layers. No microservices. No event bus. No message queue. No separate worker processes.

