Phase 7 — BaseClinicRepository
repositories/base-clinic.repository.js
Every business entity belongs to a clinic. BaseClinicRepository enforces this at the data layer — controllers and services NEVER write .eq('clinic_id', ...) manually.

class BaseClinicRepository {
  constructor(table) { this.table = table; }

  // All methods require clinicId — this is the only place clinic scoping lives
  async findById(id, clinicId)
    // → WHERE id = :id AND clinic_id = :clinicId AND deleted_at IS NULL
    // → throws AppError('NOT_FOUND') if missing

  async findAll(clinicId, { filters, pagination, select, order })
    // → WHERE clinic_id = :clinicId AND deleted_at IS NULL + filters

  async create(data)
    // → INSERT ... RETURNING *

  async update(id, clinicId, data)
    // → UPDATE ... WHERE id = :id AND clinic_id = :clinicId AND deleted_at IS NULL

  async softDelete(id, clinicId, deletedBy)
    // → UPDATE SET deleted_at = NOW(), deleted_by = :deletedBy
    // → WHERE id = :id AND clinic_id = :clinicId

  async restore(id, clinicId)
    // → UPDATE SET deleted_at = NULL, deleted_by = NULL

  async count(clinicId, filters)
}
Repositories never contain business logic. They contain query logic only.

