Phase 7b — Transaction Service
services/transaction.service.js
Orchestrates multi-step operations that touch multiple repositories. This is the only place where multi-table writes happen. Repositories do single-table work; the transaction service combines them.

// Route → Controller → Transaction Service → Repositories → DB

async completeConsultation({ queueEntryId, clinicId, dentistId, patientId, procedure, diagnosis, toothNumber, totalSittings, estimatedCost, transcript, notes })
  // 1. Create treatment_plan (via TreatmentPlanRepository)
  // 2. Create visit record (via VisitRepository) ← currently MISSING, now added
  // 3. If transcript → extractPrescription → create prescription (via PrescriptionRepository)
  // 4. If totalSittings > 1 → create appointment stubs (via AppointmentRepository)
  // 5. Update queue_entry treatment_plan_id + status → 'ready_for_checkout' (via QueueRepository)
  // 6. Log to audit_log
  // On any fatal step failure: attempt to undo completed steps (compensating updates)
  // Returns { plan, visit, prescription, appointments }

async completeCheckout({ queueEntryId, clinicId, staffId, amount, paymentMethod, treatmentPlanId })
  // 1. Record payment (via PaymentRepository)
  // 2. Recalc pending_amount on treatment_plan atomically (via TreatmentPlanRepository.recalcPendingAmount)
  // 3. Update queue_entry status → 'checked_out'
  // 4. Log to audit_log

async recordPayment({ clinicId, patientId, amount, treatmentPlanId, receivedBy, ... })
  // 1. INSERT payment
  // 2. Atomically UPDATE treatment_plan collected_amount + pending_amount
  //    Uses: SELECT FOR UPDATE (via Supabase RPC) or sequential update with optimistic lock
  // 3. Log to audit_log

async createClinic({ dentistId, clinicName, yourName, city, phone })
  // 1. Generate join_code (guaranteed unique)
  // 2. INSERT clinics
  // 3. INSERT staff (role: doctor)
  // 4. UPDATE clinics SET owner_staff_id
  // 5. UPDATE dentists name/clinic_name
  // 6. Backfill clinic_id on patients/visits/appointments/treatment_plans/prescriptions/xrays
  //    (moved from controller)
  // 7. Sign + return new V3 token

async joinClinic({ dentistId, joinCode, yourName, role })
  // 1. Lookup clinic by join_code
  // 2. INSERT staff (or return existing on 23505)
  // 3. UPDATE dentists name
  // 4. Sign + return new V3 token
Note on atomicity: Supabase JS client has no native transaction API. We simulate atomicity via:

Ordering operations so reads happen before writes
Non-fatal steps are explicitly marked and logged on failure (prescription creation, appointment stubs)
Fatal steps (treatment_plan creation) are the first write — if they fail, nothing else ran
recalcPendingAmount uses an RPC function (Postgres) to do atomic read+update: UPDATE treatment_plans SET pending_amount = GREATEST(0, estimated_cost - collected_amount) WHERE id = $1
